com.github.i49.hibiscus.common

Enum TypeId

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TypeId>
      • com.github.i49.hibiscus.common.TypeId
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TypeId>

    public enum TypeId
extends Enum<TypeId>
    Identifiers of seven built-in types available in JSON schema definitions.

    Each constants in this enumeration has a corresponding type class in com.github.i49.hibiscus.schema package. These types can be instantiated by methods provided by SchemaComponents.

    Basically, matching of types between JSON document and JSON schema will be achieved by comparing their identifiers defined in this enumeration.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ARRAY
      The identifier of JSON array type, which is represented by ArrayType class.
      BOOLEAN
      The identifier of JSON boolean type, which is represented by BooleanType class.
      INTEGER
      The identifier of JSON number without a fraction or exponent part, which is represented by IntegerType class.
      NULL
      The identifier of JSON null type, which is represented by NullType class.
      NUMBER
      The identifier of JSON number type, which is represented by NumberType class.
      OBJECT
      The identifier of JSON object type, which is represented by ObjectType class.
      STRING
      The identifier of JSON string type, which is represented by StringType class.
